1. 5 diff. b/w JavaScript & Node js 

  1. JavaScript is a client side coding. 
  1. Node js is server side coding. 

  2. Jave script is a language. 
  2. Node js is not a language it has a v8 engine that runs java script on the server side.

  3. Javescrit runs inside the browser
  3. Node js runs outside the browser

  4. Js mainly used for client side activity for web application and to provide dynamic changes in webpages
  4. Node js used to perform non-blocking operation like creating or exciting or running any backend job
 
  5. Js is Upgraded version of EXAMS script that uses chrome V8 engine written in c++
  5. Node js is written in c , c++ & JavaScript.

2. It-necessary-to-write-head-body-and-html-tags
     Ommiting HTML head & body tag was allowed by Hmtl specs.
     In the old version there is no using of head and body tags .
     Later version html2.0 did it.
     A body element's end tag may be omitted if the body element is not immediately followed by a comment
     A body element's start tag may be omitted if the element is empty, or if the first thing inside the body element is not a space character or a comment, except if the first thing inside the body element is a script or style element.
     A head start tag may be omitted if the element is empty
     A head end tag may be omitted head element is not followed by character or comment 
     Html element start tag can ommited when thing inside the html is not a comment
     Html element end tag can be omitted when the html element is immediately not followed by comment

4. 4) Execute the bellow code and write your description in txt file
        typeof(1)   = number
        typeof(1.1) = number
        typeof('1.1') = string
        typeof(true) = boolean
        typeof(null) = object
        typeof(undefined) = undefined
        typeof([]) = array 
        typeof({}) = simple object -keyvalue pair 
        typeof(NaN) = number
